• Ten percent of homes have leaks that waste 90 gallons or more per day.
•	14% of water used by homes are due to leaks.
•	A faucet that drips only once per second wastes 3,000 gallons of water each year.
•	The average home wastes 10,000 gallons of water each year due to leaks.
•	Leaks cause over one trillion gallons of water to be wasted each year in the U.S.
•	A leak just 1/32 inches in diameter can waste over 250 gallons per day.
•	A leaky toilet can use over 200 gallons per day. 
